  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nI'm trying to call `SendTransaction` with a reverting transaction but able to do so successfully? Should a reverting transaction cause a runtime exception in the simulated back-end or is this intended behavior? If it's indended, are there other ways to force a reverting transaction to signal errors?\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.9.5`\r\nOS & Version: OSX 10.14.3\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nTransaction should revert and cause a `panic` or runtime error.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nTransaction succeeds and there is a `nil` error message.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nI'm using `sendTransaction` to issue a contract transaction and then calling `sim.Commit()`. This is done with a contract that will revert upon that transaction.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\nn/a",
